reviewText:
Discovering the Secrets of Westminster in the heart of London which consists of Parliament, West Minster Abby and Big Ben, the seat of true power where beside the site of warship since 800, a royal place where every British monarch has been crowned since 1066, has witnessed art, architecture, engineering, culture, religion, politics, prosecutions, revolutions, celebrations, weddings, robberies, fires in one of the oldest democracies; offers so much information that I had to watch more than once to digest it all. Very educational and entertaining documentary. Bravo.

To see all five magnificent creations; Highclere Castle, Downton Abbey, Hampton Court Palace, Althorp and Chatsworth in five DVDs, where every single structure is full of history, architecture and interior design unmatched to any other, in truly grand scale with centuries of pride and tradition check out the link in the comment section. These are the best of the best.
An interesting look behind the scenes of a famous building.  This DVD answers many a question, and much more.

Very good video, though a bit melodramatic at times. I got it prepare for an upcoming trip to England. I'm now clued in to things that I will no doubt see in Westminster. I could have read about it, but the video was a lot of fun. I recommend this to anyone planning a trip or just interested in the Westminster area of London.
